ODE XXV

TO BACCHUS

AKE me, Bacchus, filled with thee, Where thou wilt: to grove, or grot, Cavern, or I care not what, So my theme great Caesar be.

He shall in the welkin shine,

Gain the ear of Jove on high;

I things great and fresh will try, Spoken by no lips but mine.
